23 when employees are working, to monitor and record certain air quality information in each
24 area of the facility where employees are working; and (3) take certain actions if the air quality
25 information exceeds any relevant occupational safety and health standards. Section 3 exempts
26 from those requirements state agencies and certain employers who are engaged in: (1) law
27 enforcement, firefighting or otherwise responding to emergencies; (2) solid waste
28 management or the management of hazardous waste; or (3) towing services.
