10 Sec. 3. 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, an employer who
11 has more than 15 employees who work at a large hybrid environment facility and
12 who is required to establish a written safety program pursuant to NRS 618.383
13 shall include in the written safety program provisions that:
14 (a) Require the establishment of:
15 (1) A system to mitigate exposure to greenhouse gases, other gases or
16 poor air quality that complies with all applicable occupational safety and health
17 standards established pursuant to NRS 618.295; and
18 (2) A system for monitoring employees for signs of health effects
19 resulting from exposure to greenhouses gases, other gases or poor air quality.
20 (b) Require any vehicle which is loading or unloading at the facility to have
21 the engine of the vehicle turned off, except that a refrigerated vehicle or trailer
22 with a motor that is independent of the engine of the vehicle may continue to
23 operate the motor for refrigeration.
24 (c) Require a designated person at the facility, not less than every 4 hours
25 when employees are working, to:
26 (1) Monitor the level of greenhouse gases, other gases and air quality in
27 each area of the facility where employees are working, including, without
28 limitation, any area in which employees are working in an elevated position
29 above ground level; and
30 (2) Record the level of greenhouse gases, other gases and air quality in
31 each area described in subparagraph (1) in a logbook, which must be kept at the
32 facility and available for review upon request.
33 (d) On any day when, according to the monitoring described in paragraph
34 (c), the level of greenhouse gases, other gases or air quality in any area of the
35 facility where employees are working exceeds the level set forth in any applicable
36 occupational safety and health standard established pursuant to NRS 618.295,
37 require additional fans or other forced ventilation systems be used to increase the
38 flow of air out of the facility, including, without limitation, through open loading
39 docks or bay doors.
